{"parse":{"title":"Letters, Riddles and Writs","pageid":18843975,"revid":831030553,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks vcard\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%\"><tbody><tr><th class=\"fn\" style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em;background-color: silver\"><a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Nyman\" title=\"Michael Nyman\">Michael Nyman</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.2em 0 0.4em\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_(Mostra)_(43).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flickr - nicogenin - 66\u00e8me Festival de Venise (Mostra) (43).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg/220px-Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg/330px-Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg/440px-Flickr_-_nicogenin_-_66%C3%A8me_Festival_de_Venise_%28Mostra%29_%2843%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1500\" data-file-height=\"999\" /></a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding-bottom: 0.2em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background-color: #ddd\">Operas</div><div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;text-align: left\">\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Tristram_Shandy_(opera)\" title=\"Tristram Shandy (opera)\">Tristram Shandy</a></i> (unfinished, begun 1981)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Man_Who_Mistook_His_Wife_for_a_Hat_(opera)\" title=\"The Man Who Mistook His Wife for a Hat (opera)\">The Man Who Mistook His Wife for a Hat</a></i> (1986)</li>\n<li><i><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Letters, Riddles and Writs</a></i> (1991)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Noises,_Sounds_%26_Sweet_Airs\" title=\"Noises, Sounds &amp; Sweet Airs\">Noises, Sounds &amp; Sweet Airs</a></i> (1991/3)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Facing_Goya\" title=\"Facing Goya\">Facing Goya</a></i> (2000)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Man_and_Boy:_Dada\" title=\"Man and Boy: Dada\">Man and Boy: Dada</a></i> (2003)</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Love_Counts\" title=\"Love Counts\">Love Counts</a></i> (2005)</li>\n<li><i>Sparkie: Cage and Beyond</i> (2009)</li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;padding-top:0\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Nyman_operas\" title=\"Template:Nyman operas\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Nyman_operas\" title=\"Template talk:Nyman operas\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Nyman_operas&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Letters, Riddles and Writs</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/One_act\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"One act\">one act</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Opera\" title=\"Opera\">opera</a> for television by <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Nyman\" title=\"Michael Nyman\">Michael Nyman</a>.  The story is devised by Nyman, with a <a href=\"/wiki/Libretto\" title=\"Libretto\">libretto</a> by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Jeremy_Newson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Jeremy Newson (page does not exist)\">Jeremy Newson</a> and Pat Gavin that incorporates <a href=\"/wiki/Emily_Anderson\" title=\"Emily Anderson\">Emily Anderson</a>'s English translations of <a href=\"/wiki/Letter_(message)\" title=\"Letter (message)\">correspondence</a> and other texts by <a href=\"/wiki/Wolfgang_Amadeus_Mozart\" title=\"Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart\">Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart</a>, the subject of the opera.  \n</p><p>The opera premiered on the <a href=\"/wiki/BBC\" title=\"BBC\">BBC</a> television miniseries, <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Not_Mozart&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Not Mozart (page does not exist)\">Not Mozart</a></i>, directed by Newson and Gavin.  <a href=\"/wiki/Ute_Lemper\" title=\"Ute Lemper\">Ute Lemper</a> played the role of Mozart.  Nyman appears as a court <a href=\"/wiki/Pianist\" title=\"Pianist\">pianist</a> instructed to play an \"offending extract\" of the <i>String Quart in E flat major, K. 428</i> when <a href=\"/wiki/Joseph_Haydn\" title=\"Joseph Haydn\">Joseph Haydn</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Julian_Glover\" title=\"Julian Glover\">Julian Glover</a>) accuses Mozart of musical <a href=\"/wiki/Plagiarism\" title=\"Plagiarism\">plagiarism</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Court\" title=\"Court\">court</a>, and Mozart complains that Nyman has slowed down his <a href=\"/wiki/Chord_(music)\" title=\"Chord (music)\">chords</a>.  This section of the opera is an <a href=\"/wiki/Opera_buffa\" title=\"Opera buffa\">opera buffa</a>-style interlude.  The majority of the opera is more serious.  Extracts of the opera are featured on <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Michael_Nyman_Songbook\" title=\"The Michael Nyman Songbook\">The Michael Nyman Songbook</a></i> and <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mozart_252\" title=\"Mozart 252\">Mozart 252</a></i>.\n</p><p>The film also features <a href=\"/wiki/David_Thomas_(singer)\" title=\"David Thomas (singer)\">David Thomas</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Bass-baritone\" title=\"Bass-baritone\">bass-baritone</a>) as <a href=\"/wiki/Leopold_Mozart\" title=\"Leopold Mozart\">Leopold Mozart</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Tony_Rohr\" title=\"Tony Rohr\">Tony Rohr</a> as <a href=\"/wiki/Ludwig_van_Beethoven\" title=\"Ludwig van Beethoven\">Ludwig van Beethoven</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Letters,_Riddles_and_Writs&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0102290/\"><i>Letters, Riddles and Writs</i></a> on <a href=\"/wiki/IMDb\" title=\"IMDb\">IMDb</a>&#32;</li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg/30px-Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg\" width=\"30\" height=\"45\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg/45px-Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg/60px-Lyceum_Theatre_1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2304\" data-file-height=\"3456\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about an English language <a href=\"/wiki/Opera\" title=\"Opera\">opera</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Letters,_Riddles_and_Writs&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:English-opera-stub\" title=\"Template:English-opera-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li